x4freetext: The scattering samples were right cylinders of 2.5 cm
to 3.5 cm in diam. and  3 to 4 cm long, were placed
vertically about 12 cm from the target.
A well shielded NE213 liquid scintillator of
5 inch diameter and 2 inch thick, incorporating two
2 MeV bias respectively coupled to Hamamatsu R1250
photomultiplier tube. Detector efficiency was deter-
mined to +- 4% by combining the calculation
and the measurement of fission spectrum from Cf-252
The T(d,n) reaction using a solid Ti-T target
at 90 or 97. 5 and 0 degrees for 14.1 and 18.2 MeV
measurement respectively. A small NE213 scintillator
monitored the source neutrons for flux normalization.
Neutrons of energy 14.1 and 18 MeV respectively.
